HEADWORD: Ad captandum
<hw>Ad cap*tan"dum</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[L., for
catching.]</ety> <def>A phrase used adjectively sometimes of
meretricious attempts to catch or win popular favor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

